paragraphs.title: Loading data set to /tmp/ directory (local)
paragraphs.text:
%sh


#2013
wget https://github.com/rvm-courses/GasPrices/blob/master/Prix2013.zip?raw=true -O /tmp/2013.zip

%sh

#2014
wget https://github.com/rvm-courses/GasPrices/blob/master/Prix2014.zip?raw=true -O /tmp/2014.zip

%sh

#2015
wget https://github.com/rvm-courses/GasPrices/blob/master/Prix2015.zip?raw=true -O /tmp/2015.zip

%sh

#2016
wget https://github.com/rvm-courses/GasPrices/blob/master/Prix2016-1204.zip?raw=true -O /tmp/2016.zip

paragraphs.title: Merging all the csv files
paragraphs.text:
%sh

mkdir /tmp/project

unzip /tmp/*.zip | cat *.csv |sed 's|;|,|g'> /tmp/project/prix_gas.csv

  #pdv_id,pdv_cp,pdv_pop,pdv_latitude,pdv_longitude,prix_maj,prix_id,prix_nom,prix_valeur
  #sed '1i\pdv_id,pdv_cp,pdv_pop,pdv_latitude,pdv_longitude,prix_maj,prix_id,prix_nom,prix_valeur\'

paragraphs.title: Loading xml daily data to local
paragraphs.text:
%sh

wget https://donnees.roulez-eco.fr/opendata/jour -O /tmp/daily_data.zip

paragraphs.title: Formatting daily data
paragraphs.text:
%sh

rm /tmp/project/*.xml

unzip /tmp/daily_data.zip | cat *.xml | sed '1d'|sed '/<adresse/d' |sed '/<ville/d'|sed '/<ouverture/d'|sed '/<service/d'| sed '/<services/d'|sed '/<\/services>/d'|sed '/<fermeture/d'| sed '/<rupture/d'| sed '/<prix\/>/d'|sed '/<pdv_liste>/d' | sed '/<\/pdv_liste>/d' | sed 's/^[[:space:]]*//g'| awk 'BEGIN { tag = "</pdv>" ; pdv_line = ""; change_pdv = "true"; FS = "\n";} {if(change_pdv == "true") { pdv_line=$0; change_pdv = "false";} if($0 != tag && $0 != pdv_line && $0 != "") { $0=pdv_line$0; print $0;} else if($0 == tag){change_pdv = "true";}}' | sed 's|/>|/></pdv>|g'> /tmp/project/formattedDailyData.xml

%hive

CREATE TABLE gasdata (
pdv_id  int,
pdv_cp string,
pdv_pop string ,
pdv_latitude int, 
pdv_longitude int,
prix_maj string,
prix_id  int,
prix_nom string,
prix_valeur int)

ROW FORMAT DELIMITED FIELDS TERMINATED BY ','

%hive

load data local

inpath '/tmp/project/prix_gas.csv' 

into table gasdata

//Because of the gasdata table size, it is time consuming to execute query !!
//We will use the xml formatted daily data for the visualizations

%hive


load data local

inpath '/tmp/project/formattedDailyData.xml' 

into table xmldata

%hive

CREATE TABLE dailyData(
    pdv_id int,
    pdv_latitude int,
    pdv_longitude int,
    pdv_cp int,
    pdv_pop string,
    prix_nom string,
    prix_id int,
    prix_maj string,
    prix_valeur int)
    ROW FORMAT DELIMITED
    STORED AS PARQUET

%hive

INSERT OVERWRITE TABLE dailyData SELECT // inserting the xml data
    xpath_int(d_data, 'pdv/@id'),
    xpath_int(d_data, 'pdv/@latitude'),
    xpath_int(d_data, 'pdv/@longitude'),
    xpath_int(d_data, 'pdv/@cp'),
    xpath_string(d_data, 'pdv/@pop'),
    xpath_string(d_data, 'pdv/prix/@nom'),
    xpath_int(d_data, 'pdv/prix/@id'),
    xpath_string(d_data, 'pdv/prix/@maj'),
    xpath_int(d_data, 'pdv/prix/@valeur')
    from xmldata

%hive


truncate table xmldata

paragraphs.title: Average Price Per Id
paragraphs.text:
%hive

select pdv_id, avg(prix_valeur) as average_price

from dailydata 

group by pdv_id

paragraphs.title: Average price per name
paragraphs.text:
%hive

select prix_nom, avg(prix_valeur) as average_price
from dailydata
group by prix_nom

%hive
select pdv_pop, avg(prix_valeur) as average_valeur
from dailydata
group by pdv_pop

%hive
select pdv_pop, count(prix_nom) as nbre_name
from dailydata
group by pdv_pop
